     FateCall v1.0 Copyright (C)1994 by Fate/tRiflEX All Rights reserved

Looks nice, eh? Display "FateCall.iff" for a coloured Version.
Some more Features:

+ Random Select of Headers
  Every Caller can get another Ansi, or, e.g. if you're using NTSC,
  a different Quote at the Top of the Screen.
+ Auto-Size Converting from KB to MB
+ Nearly unreachable Limits... or did your Users already upload more than
  99999 MB? :)
+ Uses ONE Datafile which you display directly
+ Extremely configurable
+ Short, compact, optimized Code

Well, I think these are enough Reasons to use FateCall !!!

                                                  @{" How to install " link 3}
                                                  @{" Main Menu      " link Main}
@endnode
@node 3 "FateCall Guide - How to install"

Make a Directory in "PFiles:" called "FateCall".

Copy
- FateCall               - The Main Program
- FateCallChat           - Tells FateCall that somebody chatted
- FateCall.cfg           - Configuration File
- Marky.ansi             - Ansi done by Marky/Backlash^Triflex
- Maz!.ansi              - Ansi done by mAz!/UpperCases
- Nebraska.ansi          - Ansi done by Nebraska
into this Directory.

Start your favourite Text Editor and load "CNet:bbstext".
Go to Line 99 and insert at the Beginning the following:

 <CTRL-Q>#0PFiles:FateCall}

Go to Line 934 and insert at the Beginning the following:

 <CTRL-Q>#0PFiles:FateCall/FateCallChat}

Next, decide where you want the Last 10 Callers to be displayed:
- at Logon
  Enter 'wf' and 'SysText:sys.welcome'. Add the following Line:
  <CTRL-Q>*0GFiles:FateCall.dat}
- at the GFiles Section
  Enter 'ao' and add 'FateCall.dat' as a Textfile.

You are able to run FateCall right now, however I recommend modifying the
Configuration first.

                                                  @{" Configuration " link 4}
                                                  @{" Main Menu     " link Main}
@endnode
@node 4 "FateCall Guide - Configuration"

Load "PFiles:FateCall/FateCall.cfg" into the Text Editor.

----------------------------=[ File Settings ]=----------------------------

Line 01: Path and Filename of the Datafile
         Type here where you want the Last Ten Callers File to be created
         and what Name it should have.
         Default is 'GFiles:FateCall.dat'.

---------------------------=[ Colour Settings ]=---------------------------

Line 02: Colour for the Seperation Lines
         Valid for this Line and the following Lines are Values between 0-f.
         Note that on 8 Color Terminals Values between 8-f will be converted
         to the corrospending Values between 0-7.
         Default is 4.

Line 03: Colour for the User's Port Number
         Default is 1.

Line 04: Colour for the New Flag
         This Flag will be shown in front of the Name, if the User is new
         on the BBS.
         Default is 7.

Line 05: Colour for the User's Name
         Default is 2.

Line 06: Colour for the User's Group/Location
         Default is 3.

Line 07: Colour for the User's Baud (BPS) Rate
         Default is 4.

Line 08: Colour for the User's Logon Time and Minutes the User was online
         Default is 5.

Line 09: Colour for the User's Actions
         FateCall detects several Actions of the User, e.g. whether he
         uploaded or posted something.
         Default is 6.

Line 10: Colour for the User's Uploaded & Downloaded KB's/MB's
         Default is 7.

Line 11: Colour for the Today/Yesterday/Record/Total WORDS
         Default is 5.

Line 12: Colour for the Today/Yesterday/Record/Total VALUES
         Default is 3.

--------------------------=[ Language Settings ]=--------------------------

Line 13: Column Header Line
         This Line will be displayed below the Ansi/Header. It explains the
         Users what the different Values mean.
         Default is "<CTRL-Y>c7P Name<CTRL-Y>>eLocation/Group<CTRL-Y>>6BPS Logon Used Actions<CTRL-Y>>4Pumped Downed<CTRL-Y>q1"

Line 14: Actions Explanation Line
         This Line will be displayed below the Last 10 Callers and explains
         what the Letters in the Actions Section mean.
         Default is "<CTRL-Y>c5* <CTRL-Y>c4[<CTRL-Y>c1E<CTRL-Y>c4]<CTRL-Y>c7Mail <CTRL-Y>c4[<CTRL-Y>c1B<CTRL-Y>c4]<CTRL-Y>c7ase <CTRL-Y>c4[<CTRL-Y>c1G<CTRL-Y>c4]<CTRL-Y>c7Files <CTRL-Y>c4[<CTRL-Y>c1P<CTRL-Y>c4]<CTRL-Y>c7Files <CTRL-Y>c4[<CTRL-Y>c1C<CTRL-Y>c4]<CTRL-Y>c7hats <CTRL-Y>c4[<CTRL-Y>c1U<CTRL-Y>c4]<CTRL-Y>c7pload <CTRL-Y>c4[<CTRL-Y>c1D<CTRL-Y>c4]<CTRL-Y>c7ownload <CTRL-Y>c4[<CTRL-Y>c1L<CTRL-Y>c4]<CTRL-Y>c7ost Carrier <CTRL-Y>c5*"

Line 15: What to say for "Today Calls"
         Always start with '<CTRL-Y>c' and the Number you specified in Line
         11. Note the String MUST be 14 Chars long (including the CTRL-Y).
         Use Space if you use less.

Line 16: What to say for "Today Uploads"
         Here you don't need the "<CTRL-Y>c"..., just the Words.
         This String must be 13 Chars long.

Line 17: What to say for "Today Downloads"
         This String must be 15 Chars long.

Line 18: What to say for "Y'day Calls" (Yesterday Calls)
         Here you need "<CTRL-Y>c" and Line 11's Number again.
         This String must be 14 Chars long (again).

Line 19: What to say for "Y'day Uploads"
         This String must be... guess... yes, 13 Chars long.

Line 20: What to say for "Y'day Downloads"
         This String must be... hmmm... 15 Chars long :)

Line 21: What to say for "Recrd Calls" (Record Calls)
         You need the "<CTRL-Y>c" again.
         Indeed, 14 Chars.

Line 22: What to say for "Recrd Uploads" (13 Chars)

Line 23: What to say for "Recrd Downloads" (15 Chars)
         
Line 24: What to say for "Total Calls" (14 Chars) (CTRL-Y !)

Line 25: What to say for "Total Uploads" (13 Chars)

Line 26: What to say for "Total Downloads" (15 Chars)

---------------------------=[ Sysop Settings ]=---------------------------

Line 27: Log the Sysop?
         Specify '0' for "No", any Value bigger than 1 for "Yes". Specify
         '1' and you will be asked everytime you log off.
         Default is 0.

Line 28: Access Level of Sysop
         If you wish to make the Setting in Line 27 become active for your
         Cosysop(s), specify here the Access Level your Cosysop(s) have.
         Default is 23.

---------------------=[ Random Ansi/Header Settings ]=---------------------

Line 29: Number of Headers/Ansis for the Random Generator.
         Default is 3.

Line 30: Here the Headers are placed. To display an Ansi just use the
 - ...   MCI Command * to display an Ansi.
         Defaults are these 3 Lines:
         *0PFiles:FateCall/Marky.ansi
         *0PFiles:FateCall/Maz!.ansi
         *0PFiles:FateCall/Nebraska.ansi

So if you want to add an Ansi, increase the Number in Line 29 and add a
Line to the End of the Configfile saying
 <CTRL-Q>*0DH0:MyAnsi.txt}
and you're finished.

I'm sorry, but I didn't have the Time to explain this that good.
Anyway, if you have any Problems with the Configuration, don't hestigate to
contact me!

